This solution works because the largest power of 3 that can fit in an int is 3^19 (which is approximately 1.2 billion). If n is a power of 3, then it must be a multiple of 3^19. We can check this by taking the logarithm of n with base 3 and checking if the result is an integer. If it is, then n is a power of 3.

